            "title": "GSK plc completed the acquisition of 35Pharma Inc.",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\">\n        \n                    GSK plc (LSE:GSK) entered an agreement to acquire 35Pharma Inc. for $950 million on February 25, 2026. Under the terms of the agreement, GSK will acquire 100% of the equity of 35Pharma Inc. for $950 million, payable in cash at closing. The acquisition includes HS235, a potential best-in-class investigational medicine that has completed phase I healthy volunteer clinical trials with studies to start imminently in pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH) and pulmonary hypertension due to heart failure with preserved ejection fraction (PH-HFpEF).<br/><br/>\n\nThe transaction is subject to customary conditions, including applicable regulatory agency clearances under the Hart-Scott-Rodino Act in the US and the Competition Act in Canada, along with a filing under the Investment Canada Act. <br/><br/>\n\nJamie Leigh, Rowook Park, Lindsey O?Crump, Michael Tuscan, Ben Beerle, Div Gupta, Ryan Sansom, Barbara Mirza, Christophe Beauduin, Megan Browdie, and Todd Gluth of Cooley LLP acted as legal advisor for 35Pharma Inc. Stikeman Elliott LLP acted as legal advisor for 35Pharma Inc. Centerview Partners LLC and J.P. Morgan Securities LLC acted as Financial advisor for 35Pharma Inc.<br/><br/>\n\nGSK plc (LSE:GSK) completed the acquisition of 35Pharma Inc. on April 15, 2026.\n    \n    </div>",
